Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "beti" in different forms and positions:

1. Ona *bije* svoj omiljeni bubanj. (She *beats* her favorite drum.)
2. U ovoj šumi možeš *čuti* ptice kako *cvrkuću* i kako voda *teče*. (In this forest, you can *hear* birds *chirping* and water *flowing*.)
3. Svi smo *bili* iznenađeni kad smo čuli tu vest. (We were all *surprised* when we heard that news.)
4. *Beto* je ime koje sam izabrao za svog novog psa. (*Beto* is the name I chose for my new dog.)
5. Moram da *idem* kući jer mi je danas rano ustajanje. (I have to *go* home because I have an early morning tomorrow.)

